      "@deontologician That wouldn't work. The whole thing needs to be deterministic, because it will be executed independently on every replica. If each execution can lead to different results, then we'll get divergence between replicas.\r\n\r\nAs a secondary concern, the function should also be efficient since we will be holding a write lock on the leaf node and globally on all secondary indexes of the table while we're evaluating it."
